 Sector, Althowra Daily.\n\n==Publications in the field of travel writing==\n\n*Journey to the Lost Paradise, Andalusia.\n*Journey to the City of two Continents, Istanbul.\n*Journey to the Paradise which Adam lost, Bali.\n\n== Other Activities==\n\n*Participated in several discussions of topics related to economics and Political Economy.\n*Participated in several Economic conferences in Yemen and around the world.\n\n==See also==\n*[[Economy of Yemen]]\n*[[Yemeni rial]]\n*[[Central Bank of Yemen]]\n\n== References ==\n{{Refbegin}}\n* http://www.centralbank.gov.ye/news.aspx?keyid=63&pid=60&lang=1&cattype=2\n* https://archive.is/20130105182812/http://www.yobserver.com/business-and-economy/10012882.html\n* http://www.ifc.org/IFCExt/pressroom/IFCPressRoom.nsf/0/E8AC0F0757541A338525757B00592DEF?\n* http://www.al-tagheer.com/news.php?id=14521\n* http://archives.mees.com/issues/743/articles/29219\nOpenDocument\n* https://web.archive.org/web/20110531154203/http://www.amf.org.ae/content/governors\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Samawi, Ahmed A.}}\n[[Category:1946 births]]\n[[Category:Yemeni economists]]\n[[Category:Central bankers]]\n[[Category:Governors of the Central Bank of Yemen]]\n[[Category:Finance ministers of Yemen]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:20th-century economists]]\n[[Category:Alumni of the University of Manchester]]\n[[Category:Alexandria University alumni]]\n[[Category:People from Dhamar Governorate]]\n[[Category:20th-century Yemeni people]] \n[[Category:21st-century Yemeni people]]\n\n{{Yemen-politician-stub}}\n{{asia-economist-stub}}\n{{Yemen-bio-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Ser Amantio di Nicolao", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eReferences:add authority control", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ahmed_Abdul_Rahman_Al-Samawi"}
{"title_page": "Gilleleje station", "text_new": "{{unreferenced|date=May 2015}}\n{{Infobox station\n| name          = Gilleleje\n| type          = [[Railway station]]\n| style         = STL\n| image         = Gilleleje_Station_TRS.jpg\n| image_caption = Front facade of Gilleleje station\n| address       = Gilleleje Stationsvej 10<br>3250 [[Gilleleje]]\n| country = Denmark\n| coordinates   = {{coord|56.1237|12.3030|region:DK|format=dms|display=inline,title}}\n| map_type      = Denmark\n| line          = [[Hornb\u00e6k Line]]\n| other         = \n| opened        = 14 May 1896\n| closed        = \n| rebuilt       = 16 January 1918\n| code          = \n| platform      = 2\n| tracks        = 3\n| owned         = [[Hovedstadens Lokalbaner]]\n| operator      = [[Lokaltog]]\n| services      = {{s-rail|title=Lokaltog}}\n{{s-line|system=Lokaltog|line=Hornb\u00e6k Line|previous=Gilleleje East|next=}}\n{{s-line|system=Lokaltog|line=Gribskov Line|branch=Gilleleje|previous=Fjellenstrup|next=}}\n}}\n'''Gilleleje station''' ({{IPA-da|kil\u02c8l\u0251j\u026a st\u00e6\u02c8\u0255o\u02c0n}}) is the main [[railway station]] serving the [[fishing port]] and [[seaside resort]] [[town]] of [[Gilleleje]] on the north coast of [[Zealand]], [[Denmark]]. \n\nThe station is the [[terminal train station|terminus]] of the [[Hornb\u00e6k Line]] from [[Helsing\u00f8r]] to [[Gilleleje]] and of the Gilleleje branch of the [[Gribskov Line]] from [[Hiller\u00f8d]] to Gilleje. The train services are currently operated by the [[railway company]] [[Lokaltog]] which runs frequent [[local train]] services from Gilleleje to [[Helsing\u00f8r station]] and [[Hiller\u00f8d station]].\n\n==External links==\n{{commonscat|Gilleleje Station}}\n*[http://www.lokaltog.dk Lokaltog]\n{{Gribskov Municipality}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Gilleleje station}}\n[[Category:Railway stations in Denmark]]\n[[Category:Buildings and structures in Gribskov Municipality]]\n[[Category:Railway stations opened in 1896]]\n[[Category:1896 establishments in Denmark]]\n", "text_old": "{{unreferenced|date=May 2015}}\n{{Infobox station\n| name          = Gilleleje\n| type          = [[Railway station]]\n| style         = STL\n| image         = Gilleleje_Station_TRS.jpg\n| image_caption = Front facade of Gilleleje station\n| address       = Gilleleje Stationsvej 10<br>3250 [[Gilleleje]]\n| country = Denmark\n| coordinates   = {{coord|56.1237|12.3030|region:DK|format=dms|display=inline,title}}\n| map_type      = Denmark\n| line          = [[Hornb\u00e6k Line]]\n| other         = \n| opened        = 14 May 1896\n| closed        = \n| rebuilt       = 16 January 1918\n| code          = \n| platform      = 2\n| tracks        = 3\n| owned         = [[Hovedstadens Lokalbaner]]\n| operator      = [[Lokaltog]]\n| services      = {{s-rail|title=Lokaltog}}\n{{s-line|system=Lokaltog|line=Hornb\u00e6k Line|previous=Gilleleje East|next=}}\n{{s-line|system=Lokaltog|line=Gribskov Line|branch=Gilleleje|previous=Fjellenstrup|next=}}\n}}\n'''Gilleleje station''' ({{IPA-da|kil\u02c8laj\u026a st\u00e6\u02c8\u0255o\u02c0n}}) is the main [[railway station]] serving the [[fishing port]] and [[seaside resort]] [[town]] of [[Gilleleje]] on the north coast of [[Zealand]], [[Denmark]]. \n\nThe station is the [[terminal train station|terminus]] of the [[Hornb\u00e6k Line]] from [[Helsing\u00f8r]] to [[Gilleleje]] and of the Gilleleje branch of the [[Gribskov Line]] from [[Hiller\u00f8d]] to Gilleje. The train services are currently operated by the [[railway company]] [[Lokaltog]] which runs frequent [[local train]] services from Gilleleje to [[Helsing\u00f8r station]] and [[Hiller\u00f8d station]].\n\n==External links==\n{{commonscat|Gilleleje Station}}\n*[http://www.lokaltog.dk Lokaltog]\n{{Gribskov Municipality}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Gilleleje station}}\n[[Category:Railway stations in Denmark]]\n[[Category:Buildings and structures in Gribskov Municipality]]\n[[Category:Railway stations opened in 1896]]\n[[Category:1896 establishments in Denmark]]